2summary%22%3A%22PM%20Modi%20takes%20oath%3A%20President%20Droupadi%20Murmu%20administered%20the%20oaths%20of%20office%20and%20secrecy%20to%20the%20newly%20appointed%20members%20of%20the%20Council%20of%20Ministers%20at%20the%20ceremony%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fpolitics%2Fmodi-govt-s-third-term-jp-nadda-chirag-paswan-join-cabinet-full-list-124061000147_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fpolitics%2Fmodi-govt-s-third-term-jp-nadda-chirag-paswan-join-cabinet-full-list-124061000147_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fpolitics%2Fmodi-govt-s-third-term-jp-nadda-chirag-paswan-join-cabinet-full-list-124061000147_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BTo%20Flatter%20Putin's%20Ego''%3A%20Why%20Are%20Top%20Scientists%20In%20Russia%20Being%20Jailed%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20Russia%20has%20arrested%20at%20least%20a%20dozen%20scientists%20and%20physicists%20on%20suspicion%20of%20high%20treason.%20According%20to%20the%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc8001gvp4dpo%5C%22%3E%20BBC%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20three%20out%20of%20a%20dozen%20have%20already%20died%20in%20custody%20but%20the%20mystery%20remains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20elderly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussia-jails-hypersonic-scientist-for-14-years-on-treason-charges-5713007%5C%22%3ERussian%20physicist%20Anatoly%20Maslov%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20sentenced%20to%2014%20years%20in%20a%20penal%20colony%20for%20treason%2C%20the%20latest%20of%20a%20string%20of%20cases%20against%20experts%20working%20on%20the%20science%20that%20underpins%20Russia's%20development%20of%20hypersonic%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20renowned%20Russian%20scientist%20Alexander%20Kuranov%20received%20a%20seven-year%20sentence%20in%20a%20high-security%20prison%20for%20state%20treason.%20The%20director%C2%A0of%20the%20Khristianovich%20Institute%20of%20Theoretical%20and%20Applied%20Mechanics%20(ITAM)%20in%20Novosibirsk%20Siberia%2C%20Alexander%20Shiplyuk%20was%20also%20arrested%20in%20August%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20scientists%20had%20conducted%20theoretical%20work%20in%20areas%20relevant%20to%20the%20development%20of%20hypersonic%20missiles%20-%20cutting-edge%20weapons%20capable%20of%20carrying%20payloads%20at%20up%20to%2010%20times%20the%20speed%20of%20sound%20to%20punch%20through%20air%20defence%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELawyer%20Yevgeny%20Smirnov%20of%20Pervy%20Otdel%20(First%20Department)%2C%20an%20association%20that%20specialises%20in%20defending%20people%20in%20cases%20of%20treason%20and%20espionage%2C%20said%20the%20charges%20against%20the%20three%20scientists%20were%20approximately%20the%20same%20-%20spilling%20information%20considered%20a%20state%20secret%20while%20participating%20in%20an%20international%20conference%20or%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Kremlin%20called%20the%20accusations%20''serious''%2C%C2%A0colleagues%20and%20defence%20lawyers%20said%20the%20scientists%20weren't%20involved%20in%20weapons%20development.%20In%20an%20open%20letter%2C%20they%20decried%20their%20arrests%2C%C2%A0saying%20that%20the%20three%20men%20had%20merely%20participated%20in%20overseas%20conferences%20and%20international%20projects%20and%20that%20they%20had%20their%20work%20published%20in%20popular%20magazines.%20The%20letter%20also%20said%20they%20were%20known%20for%20''brilliant%20scientific%20results%26quot%3B%20and%20had%20''always%20remained%20faithful''%20to%20their%20country's%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20are%20still%20expected%20to%20publish%20internationally%20and%20collaborate%20with%20foreign%20colleagues%2C%20%26quot%3Bmeanwhile%2C%20the%20FSB%20thinks%20contact%20with%20foreign%20scientists%20and%20writing%20for%20foreign%20journals%20is%20a%20betrayal%20of%20the%20Motherland%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20arrested%20scientists'%20colleagues%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E''We%20just%20don't%20understand%20how%20to%20continue%20doing%20our%20job.%20What%20we%20are%20rewarded%20for%20today%E2%80%A6%20tomorrow%20becomes%20the%20reason%20for%20criminal%20prosecution%2C''%20their%20open%20letter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYevgeny%20Smirnov%2C%20a%20lawyer%20with%20First%20Division%2C%20a%20Russian%20human%20rights%20and%20legal%20organisation%2C%20said%20that%2C%20in%20private%20conversations%2C%20FSB%20officers%20have%20admitted%20to%20him%20that%20cases%20about%20sharing%20hypersonic%20secrets%20were%20being%20opened%20%26quot%3Bto%20satisfy%20the%20wishes%20of%20those%20higher%20up%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20believes%20the%20FSB%20wants%20to%20give%20the%20impression%20that%20spies%20are%20hunting%20Russian%20missile%20secrets%20%26quot%3Bto%20flatter%20the%20ego%26quot%3B%20of%20Mr%20Putin.%C2%A0Mr%20Smirnov%20added%20that%20the%20FSB%20sometimes%20offers%20more%20lenient%20sentences%20if%20suspects%20confess%20and%20implicate%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.themoscowtimes.com%2F2023%2F05%2F16%2F3-russian-hypersonic-missile-scientists-jailed-for-treasoncolleagues-say-a81155%5C%22%3EMoscow%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20treason%20cases%20are%20heard%20behind%20closed%20doors%20in%20Russia%20as%20they%20deal%20with%20what%20authorities%20deem%20to%20be%20classified%20information.%20Those%20found%20guilty%20face%20a%20maximum%20prison%20sentence%20of%2020%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717993080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fqpik48gg_russian-physicist_625x300_21_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fto-flatter-putins-ego-why-are-top-scientists-