t-exploration-volcanoes-life%5C%22%3ESpace.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20report%20stated%20that%20the%20image%20of%20this%20mysterious%20pit%2C%20located%20on%20the%20side%20of%20the%20now-extinct%20Arsia%20Mons%20volcano%2C%20was%20captured%20by%20NASA's%20Mars%20Reconnaissance%20Orbiter%20(MRO)%20using%20a%20High-Resolution%20Imaging%20Science%20Experiment%20(HiRISE)%20camera.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20when%20NASA's%20spacecraft%20captured%20the%20image%2C%20it%20was%20just%20256%20kilometres%20(159%20miles)%20from%20Mar's%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThis%20mysterious%20hole%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20a%20vertical%20shaft.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20report%20stated%20that%20these%20holes%20could%20shelter%20the%20astronauts%20in%20the%20future.%20Reasoning%20this%2C%20the%20report%20claimed%2C%20%E2%80%9CFor%20one%2C%20they%20could%20provide%20shelter%20for%20astronauts%20in%20the%20future%3B%20because%20Mars%20has%20a%20thin%20atmosphere%20and%20lacks%20a%20global%20magnetic%20field%2C%20it%20cannot%20ward%20off%20radiation%20from%20space%20the%20way%20that%20Earth%20does.%20Consequently%2C%20radiation%20exposure%20on%20the%20Martian%20surface%20averages%20between%2040%20and%2050%20times%20greater%20than%20on%20Earth.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20addition%2C%20these%20pits%20could%20be%20helpful%20in%20giving%20information%20about%20Martian%20Life.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20other%20enticing%20aspect%20of%20these%20pits%20is%20they%20might%20not%20just%20provide%20shelter%20for%20human%20astronauts%3B%20they%20could%20hold%20astrobiological%20interest%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20they%20could%20have%20been%20sheltered%20abodes%20for%20Martian%20life%20in%20the%20past%20%E2%80%94%20perhaps%20even%20today%20if%20microbial%20life%20indeed%20exists%20there%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20presence%20of%20these%20holes%20on%20the%20side%20of%20volcanoes%20indicates%20that%20they%20are%20probably%20connected%20to%20volcanic%20activity%20on%20the%20red%20planet.%20The%20report%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CChannels%20of%20lava%20can%20flow%20away%20from%20a%20volcano%20underground%3B%20when%20the%20volcano%20grows%20extinct%2C%20the%20channel%20empties.%20That%20leaves%20behind%20a%20long%2C%20underground%20tube.%20We%20see%20such%20tubes%20not%20only%20on%20Mars%20but%20also%20on%20the%20moon%20and%20on%20Earth.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIt%20still%20remains%20a%20mystery%20how%20deep%20these%20holes%20descend.%20In%20addition%2C%20it%20is%20also%20unclear%20whether%20these%20holes%20open%20into%20a%20large%20cavern%20or%20they%20are%20contained%20to%20a%20small%2C%20cylindrical%20depression.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20report%20concluded%20by%20saying%20that%20if%20these%20pits%20open%20up%20into%20caves%2C%20in%20future%20they%20may%20become%20a%20preferable%20landing%20site%20for%20crewed%20missions%20to%20Mars.%20Such%20a%20mission%20would%20require%20the%20astronauts%20to%20build%20a%20sheltered%20base%20camp%20far%20from%20the%20world's%20unrelenting%20radiation.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717982340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fru68bbb8_mysterious-hole-on-mars-_625x300_10_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fmysterious-hole-on-mars-could-shelter-humans-during-crewed-mission-5852267%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20National%20Aeronautics%20and%20Space%20Administration%20(NASA)%20has%20captured%20a%20mysterious%20hole%20on%20Mars.%20This%20pit%20on%20the%20flank%20of%20an%20ancient%20volcano%20is%20a%20few%20meters%20across%20and%20was%20originally%20discovered%20on%20August%2015%202022%2C%20reported%20Space.com.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2F