essinsider.com%2Fisrael-added-to-un-blacklist-for-childrens-rights-violations-2024%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Feral%20cats%20have%20taken%20over%20Puerto%20Rico's%20Old%20San%20Juan.%20But%20residents%20are%20rolling%20their%20eyes%20at%20a%20plan%20to%20remove%20them.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223888%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22San%20Juan%20cats%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6665dae2ed9a404d829bf998%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222592%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOne%20of%20the%20many%20feral%20cats%20of%20Old%20San%20Juan.%3Cp%3EApril%20Stevenson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFeral%20cats%20have%20long%20been%20a%20part%20of%20the%20landscape%20in%20the%20historic%20areas%20of%20Old%20San%20Juan.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20the%20National%20Park%20Service%20is%20forging%20ahead%20with%20a%20plan%20to%20remove%20the%20cats.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20advocacy%20organization%20Alley%20Cat%20Allies%20in%20March%20sued%20the%20park%20service%20over%20the%20plan.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20generations%2C%20feral%20cats%20have%20wandered%20the%20historic%20Old%20San%20Juan%20neighborhood%20in%20San%20Juan%2C%20Puerto%20Rico%20%E2%80%94%20attracting%20their%20share%20of%20local%20fans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20National%20Park%20Service%2C%20however%2C%20is%20not%20one%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20agency%20is%20moving%20forward%20with%20a%20plan%20to%20remove%20the%20cats%20from%20the%20San%20Juan%20National%20Historic%20Site%20%E2%80%94%20which%20includes%20the%20imposing%20Castillo%20San%20Felipe%20del%20Morro%20and%20Castillo%20San%20Crist%C3%B3bal%20%E2%80%94%20despite%20protests%20from%20many%20longtime%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%3F%20The%20agency%20said%20in%2020222%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nps.gov%2Fsaju%2Flearn%2Fnews%2Fenvironmental-assessment-for-paseo-del-morro-free-ranging-cats.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20cats%20inhabiting%20the%20area%20were%20%26quot%3Bnot%20ideal%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20especially%20at%20the%20touristy%20Paseo%20del%20Morro%2C%20and%20that%20their%20living%20situation%20is%20%26quot%3Binconsistent%20with%20National%20Park%20Service%20policies%20regarding%20the%20feeding%20of%20animals%20and%20invasive%20species.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20also%20said%20it%20sought%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20of%20animal%20abandonment.%20However%2C%20the%20roughly%20200%20cats%20have%20become%20a%20beloved%20part%20of%20the%20neighborhood%20by%20tourists%20and%20natives%20alike%2C%20and%20many%20locals%20say%20their%20displacement%20is%20reminiscent%20of%20broader%20and%20more%20ominous%20changes%20in%20Old%20San%20Juan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20home%20to%20artists%2C%20Old%20San%20Juan%20%E2%80%94%20with%20its%20colorful%20colonial%20architecture%20and%20cobblestone%20streets%20%E2%80%94%20has%20been%20invaded%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F06%2F08%2Fus%2Fpuerto-rico-old-san-juan-cats.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshort-term%20rentals%20and%20vacation%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20The%20New%20York%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20natives%20say%20they%2C%20too%2C%20could%20be%20displaced%2C%20joining%20friends%20who've%20had%20to%20leave%20Old%20San%20Juan%20due%20to%20rising%20costs%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20residents%2C%20the%20possibility%20that%20Old%20San%20Juan%20will%20lose%20its%20feral%20cats%20only%20adds%20to%20the%20feeling%20that%20the%20neighborhood%20is%20losing%20its%20way%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20not%20every%20resident%20loves%20the%20cats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20park%20service%20announced%20its%20plan%2C%20one%20Old%20San%20Juan%20resident%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20cats%20create%20areas%20where%20they%20accumulate%20their%20e